## How to amend a commit in the stack with git branchless

The branchless tool's `git amend` only works on the current HEAD.
To amend a non-HEAD commit in the stack, use this workflow:

1. Stash any working-tree changes:
       git stash

2. Switch to the target commit (naturally results in detached HEAD):
       git switch <target-commit-hash>

3. Pop your stash:
       git stash pop

4. Stage changes and amend:
       git add <files...>
       git amend

   Branchless will automatically restack all descendant commits
   in-memory (or fall back to on-disk if there are merge conflicts).
   If conflicts occur, run:
       git restack --merge

5. Switch back to the branch tip:
       git switch <branch-name>

6. Verify with dzil test.

Key points:
- Use `git switch -d` (not `git checkout`) for detached HEAD
- Files not touched by descendant commits restack cleanly in-memory
- If descendant commits touch the same files, use `git restack --merge`
  to resolve conflicts (or `git restack` for automatic in-memory rebase)
- After restack, the branch tip moves to include the rebased stack

